ActCanadian Environmental Protection Act, 1999
SubjectOrder Declaring that the Reduction of Carbon Dioxide Emissions from Coal-fired Generation of Electricity Regulations Do Not Apply in Saskatchewan
PrecisORDER DECLARING THAT THE REDUCTION OF CARBON DIOXIDE EMISSIONS FROM COAL-FIRED GENERATION OF ELECTRICITY REGULATIONS do not apply in Saskatchewan in order to reduce regulatory overlap and reporting burden, while allowing Saskatchewan to achieve equivalent greenhouse gas emissions reductions in a manner that best suits its particular circumstances.
